at best, very little of that which has remained of the acidum. The
other, however, will settle on the bottom without crystallising, as a
salt, which we call Alcali.
This then is the theory! We must mechanically confirm it in our
praxis, because a single substantial proof is stronger than a hundred
mere postulates or suppositions.
Take therefore a Volatile in Acidum and a dead earth that does not
contain anything, and manipulate them in the manner as follows, and
you will learn the truth.

