CHAPTER XXI
WHAT IS THE BIRTH OF ANIMALS AND OF WHAT
CONSTITUENTS THEY CONSIST AND INTO WHAT THEY
ARE AGAIN DISSOLVED.
ARBOR GENERATIONIS ANIMALIS
In this chapter we will only speak about perfect animals. All perfect
animals are engendered through motion by means of which the seen is
stimulated and allured out in the form of a viscous, watery matter, like
slime or mucus. It runs into its pertinent mother’s womb, where the
female seed is also present in order to bring forth its like. That seed
now is a thick or coagulated  and can rightly be called the animal
