in , as soon as he but leans against a certain spot?
If one considers the nature of the subterranean waters and examines
them, and concentrates a good amount of them through distillation such as the warm baths of sulphur, alum, vitriol, and saltpetre,
likewise the warm acidic springs, are they not extended corrosives?
And if someone were to concentrate and heat them just a little, then
put into them a dead chicken, would the solution not injure and peel

off the feathers together with the skin and flesh? Sweet, and also salt
water as they are, on and above the earth, would never do this.
One can indeed see it in the raw: When someone bathes too much
