know flint. If they did, they might sooner learn the Art. Flint is nearest
to lead, also to gold, because it is a sticky, mercurial-alkalised
substance, a gluten rnineralé which stands every . It could rightly
be called the ☿ of metals, which lacks nothing but Acidum to become
metallic: It is the figens fixissimum. Just give the flint a metallic colour
